# Performance

- `React.memo()` for pure components with complex props
- `useMemo()` for expensive calculations
- `useCallback()` for functions passed to optimized children
- Lazy load: `const HeavySection = lazy(() => import('./HeavySection'));`
- Images: `loading="lazy"` and explicit `width`/`height`
- Avoid inline object/array in JSX (new refs every render)

# Testing

- Test files: `ComponentName.test.js` alongside component
- Use React Testing Library; test behavior, not implementation
- Mock API at page level; test real logic in hooks
- Test accessibility (keyboard, screen reader)

# Environment

- `.env.local` for secrets (never commit)
- `.env` for public vars: `REACT_APP_*`, `VITE_*`, or `NEXT_PUBLIC_*`
- Document required env vars in README

# Security

- Never store API keys in frontend code
- Sanitize user input (prevent XSS)
- `dangerouslySetInnerHTML` only with sanitized content (DOMPurify)
- Validate file uploads (type, size)
- Use HTTPS for API calls in production
